e Expansion\t1. Launch 1 hero product 2. Test paid acquisition 3. Optimize conversion 4. Scale winners\t$3,000-$10,000\tLonger sales cycle, higher complexity Supporting Data: Brafton research shows high-ticket offers generate 3-5x more revenue per customer than low-ticket digital products Industry benchmarks indicate productized services maintain 60-75% profit margins vs. 40-50% for physical products PHASE 5: DAILY/WEEKLY OPERATIONAL CADENCE Time-Blocking Framework Day\tMorning (9am-12pm)\tAfternoon (1pm-4pm)\tEvening (4pm-6pm) Monday\t🎯 Weekly Planning: Review ClickUp, set top 3 priorities\tDeep Work: Highest ICE project\tAdmin: Emails, updates, prep Tuesday\tDeep Work: Continue top priority\tRevenue Activities: Sales calls, client delivery\tContent Creation: Marketing assets Wednesday\tDeep Work: Top priority\tRevenue Activities: Outreach, partnerships\tClickUp Review: Update progress Thursday\tDeep Work: Top priority\tProduct Development: Build/refine offers\tLearning: Industry research Friday\tBatch Work: Content, admin, small tasks\tWeekly Review: Score progress, adjust priorities\tPlanning: Next week's roadmap Weekly Review Protocol (Every Friday) Step\tAction\tTime Investment\tTool 1\tOpen ClickUp → Review all \"In Progress\" tasks\t10 min\tClickUp 2\tUpdate completion % and bottlenecks\t15 min\tClickUp custom fields 3\tMove completed items to \"Launched\"\t5 min\tDrag & drop 4\tIdentify upcoming week's Top 3 priorities\t10 min\tICE scores 5\tBlock calendar for deep work sessions\t10 min\tGoogle Calendar 6\tDocument wins and lessons learned\t10 min\tNotion/ClickUp Docs PHASE 6: AUTOMATION & INTEGRATION ClickUp Automations to Set Up Automation\tTrigger\tAction\tBenefit\tSetup Path Stale Task Alert\tTask hasn't been updated in 7 days\tSend notification + move to \"Review Needed\"\tPrevents forgotten projects\tSettings → Automations → \"+ Create\" Launch Preparation\tTask moved to \"In Progress\"\tApply launch checklist template\tEnsures no steps skipped\tCustom